<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5318484>
    dc:description "Fig. 5. Cercyon kubani sp. nov.A–B dorsal and lateral habitus of paratypes from China: Yunnan: Weibaoshan; C–E – male genitalia of the holotype (C – tegmen; D – median lobe; E – sternite 9). F–I – ventral morphology (F – meso- and metaventrite; G – detail of mesoventral plate; H – prosternum and antennal groove; I – mentum)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5318484/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5318486>
    dc:description "Fig. 6. Cercyon undulipennis sp. nov. A – dorsal and lateral habitus of paratype from China: Yunnan: Gaoligong Shan; B–D – male genitalia of the holotype (B – tegmen; C – median lobe; D – sternite 9). E–H – ventral morphology (E – meso- and metaventrite; F – detail of mesoventral plate; G – mentum; H – prosternum and antennal groove)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5318486/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362729>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Cercyon kabaki Ryndevich, 2004. A–B – dorsal and lateral habitus (A – pale form from China: Sichuan: north of Dehgsheng; B – dark form from China: Sichuan: Taizping Temple); C–E – male genitalia (C – tegmen; D – median lobe; E – sternite 9); F – meso- and metaventrite; G – detail of mesoventral plate." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5362729/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5318476>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Dorsal and lateral habitus of Cercyon divisus Hebauer, 2002. A, C–D – specimens from China: Yunnan, Yulongshan; B – specimen from Nepal: Taplejung Distr., upper Simbua Khola near Tseram." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5318476/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362723>
    dc:description "Fig. 3. Cercyon flavimarginatus sp. nov.A – dorsal and lateral habitus of the paratype from China:Yunnan:Zhondian; B–D – male genitalia of the holotype (B – tegmen; C – median lobe; D – sternite 9). E–H – ventral morphology (E – meso- and metaventrite; F – detail of mesoventral plate; G – mentum; H – prosternum and antennal groove)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5362723/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5318490>
    dc:description "Fig. 7. Cercyon quisquilius (Linnaeus, 1761). A – dorsal and lateral habitus of the specimen from China: Yunnan: Lijiang; B–D – male genitalia (B – tegmen; C – median lobe; D – sternite 9). E–H – ventral morphology (E – meso- and metaventrite; F – detail of mesoventral plate; G – mentum; H – prosternum and antennal groove)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5318490/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362731>
    dc:description "Fig. 8. Cercyon unipunctatus (Linnaeus, 1758). A – dorsal and lateral habitus; B–D – male genitalia (B – tegmen; C – median lobe; D – sternite 9). E–H – ventral morphology (E – meso- and metaventrite; F – detail of mesoventral plate; G – mentum; H – prosternum and antennal groove)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5362731/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362733>
    dc:description "Fig. 9. Cercyon unipustulatus Nakane, 1982.A – dorsal and lateral habitus of the paratype from Japan: Chiba Pref., Abiko; B–D – male genitalia (B – tegmen; C – median lobe; D – sternite 9). E–H – ventral morphology of the paratype (E – meso- and metaventrite; F – detail of mesoventral plate; G – mentum; H – prosternum and antennal groove)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5362733/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362735>
    dc:description "Fig. 10. Cercyon verus Shatrovskiy, 1989.A–B – dorsal and lateral habitus of specimens from Kuril Islands; C–E – male genitalia (C – tegmen; D – median lobe; E – sternite 9). F–I – ventral morphology (F – meso- and metaventrite; G – detail of mesoventral plate; H – prosternum and antennal groove; I – mentum)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5362735/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5318478>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Cercyon divisus Hebauer, 2002. A–C – genitalia of specimen from Nepal: Taplejung Distr. (NMPC) (A – tergmen; B – median lobe; C – sternite 9). D–H – variability in the shape of male sternite 9 (D – China: Yunnan: Habashan; E – Nepal: Karnali Prov.; F – China: Yunnan: Maoniuping; G – China: Yunnan: Yulongshan; H – China: Sichuan: Moxi). I–P – ventral morphology (I–L – specimen from India: West Bengal: Darjeeling; M–P – specimen from China:Yunnan:Maoniuping):I, M – meso- and metaventrite; J, N – detail of mesoventral plate; K, O – mentum; L, P – prosternum and antennal groove." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5318478/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362739>
    dc:description "Fig. 12. Variability of elytral coloration. A–D – Cercyon unipustulatus Nakane, 1982. E–J – Cercyon verus Shatrovskiy, 1989." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5362739/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362737>
    dc:description "Fig. 11. Cercyon unipunctatus (Linnaeus, 1758), variability of the elytral coloration." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5362737/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

